comment._content: She is being towed out to sea. Possibly repaired after this in January 1912 ? - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/15304013 . On this (?) outward voyage she was carrying "35,147 bags of wheat" SMH 27/2/1912, p.10 - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/15313426 I am doubtful due to the waterline looking low.

comment.author: 33147718@N05
comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/beachcomberaustralia] Thanks for the detective work beachcomber. The waterline is looking too low to be carrying cargo you're right. The only other time it could be is 1902 (where it departed carrying coal). In May 1913 it went to Newcastle. Hmmmmm, perhaps this one is the TOURAINE in Newcastle in 1913!
